Class DoubleQueue<T>

cp213.DoubleLink<T>
cp213.DoubleQueue<T>
Type Parameters:

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>
public class DoubleQueue<T>
extends DoubleLink<T>
A simple linked queue structure of T objects. Only the T value contained in the queue is visible through the standard queue methods. Extends the DoubleLink class, which already defines the front node, rear node, length, isEmpty, and iterator.

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
      Combines the contents of the left and right Queues into the current Queue. Moves nodes only - does not move value or call the high-level methods insert or remove. left and right Queues are empty when done. Nodes are moved alternately from left and right to this Queue.
      Parameters:
      source1 - The front Queue to extract nodes from.
      source2 - The second Queue to extract nodes from.

    • combine

      public void combine​(DoubleQueue<T> source1, DoubleQueue<T> source2)

    • insert

      public void insert​(T value)
      Adds value to the rear of the queue. Increments the queue size.
      Parameters:
      value - The value to added to the rear of the queue.

    • remove

      public T remove()
      Returns the front value of the queue and removes that value from the queue. The next node in the queue becomes the new front node. Decrements the queue size.
      Returns:
      The value at the front of the queue.

    • split

      public void split​(DoubleQueue<T> target1, DoubleQueue<T> target2)
      Splits the contents of the current Queue into the left and right Queues. Moves nodes only - does not move value or call the high-level methods insert or remove. this Queue is empty when done. Nodes are moved alternately from this Queue to left and right.
      Parameters:
      target1 - The first Queue to move nodes to.
      target2 - The second Queue to move nodes to.
